{
  "stem": "1343.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In labor camps.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we lost contact with them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I did hear after the war that one of my brother was liberated by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the Russians, instead of separating them from the regular soldiers, they force marched them to-- all the way to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "During the way, more than half of them died, and then he never came home either.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My younger brother I knew was not far from me in a forced labor camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was also, I knew, liberated.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I heard the story after the war that right after the liberation, one of his friends fell into the typhoid fever.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was carrying him on his shoulder, so to speak, to a hospital, and took care of him until he recovered.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then he fell into the same sickness.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this friend of his did not wait for him or took care of him, and he died there after the war.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Which is again, another irony of fate that, you know, you survive and then you fell ill after the war.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Gyongyos, Hungary.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It is 60 miles southeast of Budapest.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It is not far from the Matra mountains, with is a resort place, was and still is in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The home, as I recall, was a very warm, caring, close-knit family home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I do believe strongly that one of the reasons I survived was that I remembered and wanted to be back at least one more Friday night with my family.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Friday nights were something, as I recall in the camp always, as a memory where table was covered with white tablecloth, the candles lit, my mother leaning over saying the blessing over the candles.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "After that, my father coming home from shul, making kiddish.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
